news.title: Shimao Group looks to repay $11.8 billion debt over 3-8 years: Sources
news.para: Shanghai-based Shimao, which first missed a public offshore bond obligation last month, is the first major Chinese developer to kick off negotiations on restructuring terms with creditors.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco earns Rs 298 crore from e-auction of four Nerul plots
news.para: ​​The sale of the fifth plot, with the biggest area of over 25,000sqm (over six acres), has been stayed by the National Green Tribunal (NGT) following protests by environmentalists as it partially falls within the CRZ.

news.title: I-T searches on premises of Phoenix group in Hyderabad
news.para: Chukkapalli Avinash and others run the group and are into top real estate projects in the city. I-T is looking into the suspected income tax evasion by the real estate firm.

news.title: Slum dwellers rush to Gujarat HC over Ahmedabad civic body's demolition bid
news.para: The AMC filed an application on July 7 and urged the HC for an early hearing on the petition filed by the slum dwellers, who have been demanding alternative accommodation if the civic body and government want to implement TP Scheme No. 5 (City Wall Improvement) Section-3.

news.title: Goa: SIT says real land owners not claiming properties
news.para: The SIT itself has registered 12 first information reports (FIRs) pertaining to land-grab, while 28 FIRs were transferred to it.

news.title: Society redevelopment law challenged in Gujarat HC
news.para: Questioning the validity of the rules, Petitioner Pragnesh Gandhi, a resident of Naranpura, stated that the authorities grant permission for redevelopment only if they have the consent of 75% of members, and that too only if the building is at least 25 years old.

news.title: Bombay HC gives fire safety panel two months to submit recommendations
news.para: The committee has to suggest which types of buildings the SCR is applicable, measures for surveillance and to protect such SCR buildings from bomb blasts and also to evacuate people in an emergency.

news.title: Nagpur: Court warns building owners of risk in absence of fire safety measures
news.para: The owners of Everest Arcade in Sakkardara, off Umred Road, mostly comprising doctors having their chambers, moved the judiciary against an order passed by the NMC’s chief fire officer (Fire and Emergency Services) under section 8(2) of the ‘Maharashtra Fire Prevention and Life Safety Measures Act, 2006’.

news.title: Noida: Supertech twin towers now fully charged for demolition
news.para: Charging of Apex and Ceyane began on August 13, with a 15-day window for completion. On Tuesday and Wednesday, expert teams will connect the explosives packed into each floor. Simultaneously, they will recheck over 20,000 connections.

news.title: Maharashtra government plans to fast-track Dharavi redevelopment, fresh bids likely soon
news.para: The redevelopment of Dharavi, Asia’s largest slum spread over 600 acres of prime land in Mumbai,  will be a big opportunity for slum-dwellers and will also help urban planners, human rights activists and the state government to transform the face of Mumbai city altogether.

news.title: Four individuals settle with Sebi case related to Sobha
news.para: Among others, it was alleged that Sobha Ltd had misrepresented the receivables for the construction of residence of one D K Shivakumar (DKS) and misreported service tax/GST dues of the individual in three financial years -- 2016-17, 2017-18 and 2018-19.

news.title: Court denies bail to businessman in Rs 34,615-crore DHFL scam
news.para: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) had earlier conducted searches at Nawandar's premises and recovered a large collection of uber-luxury watches worth crores of rupees, including Rolex Oyster Perpetual, Cartier, Omega, and Hublot, and two paintings worth Rs 33 crore, the officials said.

news.title: SC grants interim bail to ex-director of Amrapali Group
news.para: Justice Lalit clarified that a new bench will be set up after the part-heard matters are wrapped up and it would hear the rest of the issues involved in the case.

news.title: Gurugram: Project not over, Mahira Homes buyers seek meeting with top officials
news.para: The homebuyers also submitted a memorandum to the senior town planner seeking permission to allow a delegation of allottees to represent themselves at the hearing with ACS town and country planning on Tuesday in Chandigarh.

news.title: Delhi civic body will use drones to verify property details in self-assessment forms
news.para: On a pilot basis, a survey has already been carried out in Mohan Cooperative Industrial Area on Mathura Road. The services of an organisation, which conducted a similar exercise in Lucknow and Varanasi, have been roped in.
